article.headline: Army 69, Navy 50
article.story: WEST POINT, N.Y. -- Cleveland Richard scored 15 points and Chris Walker added a season-high 14, leading Army past rival Navy 69-50 on Saturday. It was Richard's career-best seventh straight game in double figures for the Black Knights (14-12, 4-8 Patriot League) while Walker also grabbed a team-high seven rebounds. Marcus Nelson recorded one blocked shot to tie the Army career record of 74 held by Jimmy Sewell (2003-07). Walker blocked three shots and stands fifth all-time with 52. The win snapped the Black Knights' three-game losing streak. O.J. Avworo and Jordan Sugars scored 13 points each for the Midshipmen (13-14, 7-5). It was Navy's lowest scoring output of the season and just the third time this year they did not score at least 60 points. Army, the league's top-ranked scoring defense, improved to 13-2 this season when keeping opponents to less than 60 points.
